title: Box Of Pullman Loaf Recipe
summary: You can never have too many hor d'oeuvre recipes, so give Box Of Pullman Loaf Recipe a try. One serving contains 267 calories, 13g of protein, and 16g of fat. This recipe serves 20 and costs 95 cents per serving. 1 person were impressed by this recipe. From preparation to the plate, this recipe takes roughly 10 minutes. A mixture of crème fraîche, eggs, eggs, and a handful of other ingredients are all it takes to make this recipe so tasty. It is a good option if you're following a pescatarian diet. All things considered, we decided this recipe deserves a spoonacular score of 36%. This score is not so spectacular. Try Pullman Loaf, Poached Eggs, Wilted Spinach and Pullman Loaf Toast with Bacon, Onion and Tomato Jam, and Buttermilk Sandwich Loaf Recipe for similar recipes.
instructions: Basically, what you are doing here is building a big box of buttered bread, a little home for your eggs. Start by removing a slice about 2 inches (5 cm) thick from the loaf. Cut off the crusts from the slice, then remove its core by cutting a square hole in the middle. Keep in mind that the hole has to be big enough to contain three scrambled eggs and the delicious fish. Preheat the oven on a low setting. Melt 1 tablespoon of the butter in a nonstick frying panor better, use a breakfast griddleover low heat and slowly color the box on all sides. Put the box on a plate along with the fish and place the plate in the oven to heat the fish and keep the box warm. In a small bowl, whisk together the eggs, cream, and a little salt and pepper. Scramble the eggs over low heat in the remaining butter in the same pan (or a new pan if you used a griddle for the bread). When they are almost set, nonchalantly add the warm pieces of fish. Heat the ensemble through. Place the ensemble in the box. Garnish with the crme frache, chives, and horseradish. We also find a teaspoon of caviar to be a nice touch.
